<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870306-0006 </DOCNO><HL> Yellow Freight Sees DropIn First-Quarter Earnings</HL><DD> 03/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> YELL </IN><DATELINE> OVERLAND PARK, Kan.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Yellow Freight System Inc. said first-quarter earnings will be &quot;substantially&quot; below the $14.2 million, or 50 cents a share, earned in the year-earlier quarter. The company wouldn't be more specific.    Raymond A. Stewart, president, cited price discounting, reduced shipping volumes and severe weather conditions, particularly on the East Coast, as reasons for the lower earnings.    The motor freight company declined to make a revenue prediction. In the yearearlier period it had revenue of about $397 million. </TEXT></DOC>